		<td>
            <span id="MainContent_DataListTypes_LabelType_88"><h2 class="title">Law Enforcer [<a href="TraitDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Law Enforcer" style="font-color: white">Link</a>]</h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy8ufc?Pathfinder-Player-Companion-Knights-of-the-Inner-Sea" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Knights of the Inner Sea pg. 27</i></a><br /><b>Requirement(s)</b> Code of Vigilance<br /> If you follow this code, you are always alert to those who transgress against the laws of civilization. You receive a +2 bonus on Sense Motive checks to gain a hunch from social situations, and begin play with a pair of masterwork manacles.<br /><br /></span>
        </td>
	</tr><tr>
		<td>
            <span id="MainContent_DataListTypes_LabelType_89"><h2 class="title"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Life of Toil [<a href="TraitDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Life of Toil" style="font-color: white">Link</a>]</h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/products/btpy8x64?Pathfinder-Roleplaying-Game-Ultimate-Campaign
" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Ultimate Campaign pg. 60</i></a><br /> You have lived a physically taxing life, working long hours for a master or to support a trade. Hard physical labor has toughened your body and mind. You gain a +1 trait bonus on Fortitude saves.<br /><br /></span>
        </td>
	</tr><tr>
		<td>
            <span id="MainContent_DataListTypes_LabelType_90"><h2 class="title"><img src="images\PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif" title="PFS Legal" style="margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;"> Lost Nobility [<a href="TraitDisplay.aspx?ItemName=Lost Nobility" style="font-color: white">Link</a>]</h2><b>Source</b> <a href="http://paizo.com/store/downloads/pathfinder/pathfinderCompanion/pathfinderRPG/v5748btpy89ca" target="_blank" class="external-link"><i>Cheliax, Empire of Devils pg. 19</i></a><br />Your family was prominent before the rise of Thrune, but that legacy is now forgotten by all but you. You hold every Chelish government official (including Hellknights) personally responsible for your lost glory. You gain a +1 trait bonus on attack and damage rolls against these officials.<br /><br /></span>
        </td>
